});
```

### 5. 🌐 CORS Not Configured
No CORS policy is set, so the API will either be inaccessible cross-origin or fully open depending on client behavior. Use the `cors` package with an explicit allowlist:

```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({ origin: ['https://your-frontend.com'] }));
```

### 6. 🔢 Hardcoded Port
